"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682269","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 23 January to the hon. Member for North Durham (Kevan Jones) (Vol 620, Col 23). Details of the Trident weapon system and submarine operations must remain secret. The Government is in no doubt about the capability and effectiveness of the Trident missile system. HMS Vengeance successfully concluded her Demonstration and Shakedown Operation and returned to the operational cycle.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","62522 ; 62523 ; 62557 ; 62563 ; 62564","2017-02-06T16:57:10.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682269/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682269/answer","20170123_UQ_on_Trident_Test_Firing.docx","20170123_UQ_on_Trident_Test_Firing.docx","Hansard extract on Trident Test Firing","Hansard extract on Trident Test Firing","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682269/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the age was of the Trident D5 II missile that was launched but unable to complete the testing as part of the 2016 Demonstration and Shakedown Operation exercise.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","62556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682270","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 23 January to the hon. Member for North Durham (Kevan Jones) (Vol 620, Col 23). Details of the Trident weapon system and submarine operations must remain secret. The Government is in no doubt about the capability and effectiveness of the Trident missile system. HMS Vengeance successfully concluded her Demonstration and Shakedown Operation and returned to the operational cycle.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","62522 ; 62523 ; 62556 ; 62563 ; 62564","2017-02-06T16:57:10.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682270/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682270/answer","20170123_UQ_on_Trident_Test_Firing.docx","20170123_UQ_on_Trident_Test_Firing.docx","Hansard extract on Trident Test Firing","Hansard extract on Trident Test Firing","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682270/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the issue that led to the Trident D5 II missile not being able to complete its testing after being launched as part of the 2016 Demonstration and Shakedown Operation exercise has now been identified.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","62557"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682271","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 26 January 2017 to the hon. Member for South Down (Ms Ritchie) to Question 61284. HMS Vengeance successfully concluded her Demonstration and Shakedown Operation and returned to the operational cycle.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","62559 ; 62560 ; 62561","2017-02-06T16:58:11.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682271/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682271/answer","20170126_61284_WQnA_extract_on_Trident_Missiles_Testing.docx","20170126_61284_WQnA_extract_on_Trident_Missiles_Testing.docx","WQnA extract on Trident Missiles Testing","WQnA extract on Trident Missiles Testing","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682271/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, who briefed the Prime Minister that a Trident D5 II missile launched as part of the 2016 Demonstration and Shakedown Operation exercise had not completed its test as planned.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","62558"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682272","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-03","<p>The UK has played a significant role in supporting the Iraqi operation which secured a notable victory over Daesh in Eastern Mosul. Since the operation began, over 450 targets in and around Mosul have been struck by the RAF.</p><p>RAF aircraft played a valuable role, using their surveillance sensors to identify civilians within the city who might be placed at particular risk and alerting the Iraqi ground forces and other Coalition aircraft to their presence. UK Service personnel have also contributed to the training of over 38,500 Iraqi forces (including more than 7,300 Peshmerga) in infantry, medical skills, C-IED measures and engineering skills, many of whom have participated in the Mosul operation.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-03T14:04:48.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682272/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682272/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682272/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Iraq: Peacekeeping Operations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to support the liberation of East Mosul; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","62637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682273","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-03","<p>Civil servants have the ability to work flexibly across Government sites where there is a business need to do so. The issuing of all passes is controlled by the local departmental security teams. Passes can also be issued to contractors or secondees based within Government premises on a case by case basis in regards to specific business needs. Numbers of passes issued directly to non-civil servants for access to departmental buildings will fluctuate over the course of a year.</p><p>Security passes are also issued to Service personnel.</p><p>Civil service passes are underpinned by a strong physical security focus, clear processes and assurance.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-03T14:05:37.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682273/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682273/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682273/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Ministry of Defence: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which persons not employed by his Department and its agencies hold security passes entitling them to enter his Department's premises.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682274","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-03","<p>Ministry of Defence policy on the publication of detailed information about operational and manning pinch points changed in 2015. Officials identified that this information had the potential to reveal vulnerabilities in the capabilities of UK Armed Forces.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-03T14:05:13.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682274/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682274/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682274/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 26 January 2017 to Question 61198, on armed forces, when his Department's policy was changed not to release that information.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682275","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-03","<p>As at 1 October 2016, there were the following numbers of personnel:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Profession </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Army</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total All Services</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Trained full-time, non-reservist doctors</p></td><td><p>321</p></td><td><p>612</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Trained full-time, non-reservist nurses (including healthcare assistants)</p></td><td><p>784</p></td><td><p>1,380</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Also, as at 1 October 2016, there were 243 civilian doctors (medical practitioners and consultants) and 396 civilian nurses (including healthcare assistants).</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-03T14:03:51.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682275/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682275/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682275/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many full-time, non-reservist (a) doctors and (b) nurses are employed by (i) the Army and (ii) his Department.","false","Biography information for Will Quince","Colchester","Will Quince","62599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682276","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH is currently undertaking harbour trials as part of her test and integration phase. This phase will demonstrate the readiness for sea of the ship's on board systems and address any technical issues, which are expected in a programme of this scale and complexity.</p><p> </p><p>Sea trials will begin to emerge on successful completion of this phase followed by her acceptance into service with the Royal Navy later in the year, as planned. It is too early at this stage to be specific about dates, which are also dependent on tides and weather conditions.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","62463","2017-02-07T16:58:45.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682276/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682276/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682276/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 2.9 of the National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 - First Annual Report 2016, published in December 2016, and his oral evidence to the Defence Select Committee of 31 January 2017, for what reason the expected start date of sea trials by HMS Queen Elizabeth has changed.","false","Biography information for Mrs Flick Drummond","Portsmouth South","Mrs Flick Drummond","62620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682277","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-06","<p>The Army is conducting a review of its Junior Entry policy to ensure it attracts the best young people and continues to maximise the talent of the individual, to the mutual advantage of both the young person and the Army. This review is expected to conclude later this year. I will place a copy of the terms of reference in the Library of the House, in due course.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-06T16:48:47.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682277/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682277/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682277/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Army: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will publish the terms of reference for the Army's Junior Entry Review; when he expects that review to report; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","62585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682278","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 31 January to the hon. Member for Rutherglen and Hamilton West (Ms Ferrier) to Question 61464. HMS Vengeance successfully concluded her Demonstration and Shakedown Operation and returned to the operational cycle.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","62565 ; 62655","2017-02-06T16:32:47.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682278/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682278/answer","20170131_61464_WQnA_extract_on_Trident_Missile_Testing.docx","20170131_61464_WQnA_extract_on_Trident_Missile_Testing.docx","61464 - WQnA extract on Trident Missile Testing","61464 - WQnA extract on Trident Missile Testing","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682278/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Trident Missiles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he was part of the discussion in which it was decided not to inform Parliament that the Trident D5 II missile launched as part of the 2016 Demonstration and Shakedown Operation exercise had not completed its test as planned.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","62562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682279","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-03","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) and Boeing are committed to working together to build prosperity, growth and exports across the country.</p><p>MOD Ministers and Boeing senior executives meet regularly to monitor and document progress on these plans. There is also frequent engagement between the company and other officials from the MOD and the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy.</p><p>On average, Boeing has hired one new person per day in the UK throughout 2015 and 2016 and that trajectory is set to continue.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-02-03T14:07:37.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682279/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682279/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Boeing: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 19 January 2017 to Question 59855, what mechanisms his Department has put in place to monitor how many of the jobs announced by Boeing at the Farnborough Air Show are created.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682280","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Department provides entitled service personnel and their families with single living accommodation or service family accommodation (SFA) either at, or close to their normal duty station. There are near 50,000 SFA properties which are used for the needs of the armed forces.</p><p>The Department also recognises the evolving housing needs of service personnel. Work to progress the Future Accommodation Model is under way to provide a more flexible accommodation offering which remains attractive to service personnel and affordable to Defence in the future.</p><p>Hotels are only ever used in exceptional circumstances to temporarily house service personnel and their families and this exceptional use is reducing.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-07T17:00:12.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682280/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682280/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to ensure that members of the armed forces and their families are not accommodated in hotels.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","62550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682281","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH is currently undertaking harbour trials as part of her test and integration phase. This phase will demonstrate the readiness for sea of the ship's on board systems and address any technical issues, which are expected in a programme of this scale and complexity.</p><p> </p><p>Sea trials will begin to emerge on successful completion of this phase followed by her acceptance into service with the Royal Navy later in the year, as planned. It is too early at this stage to be specific about dates, which are also dependent on tides and weather conditions.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","62620","2017-02-07T16:58:45.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682281/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682281/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-31","HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, during which month he expects HMS Queen Elizabeth to depart Rosyth for her first sea trials.","false","Biography information for Mrs Flick Drummond","Portsmouth South","Mrs Flick Drummond","62463"
