"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681154","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-02","<p>It is estimated that during 2013-14 approximately 300,000 employees received some income tax exemption on the first £30,000 of a payment for termination of an employment. The corresponding estimate for 2014-15 is 260,000.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-02-02T16:36:52.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681154/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681154/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-30","Redundancy Pay: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received income tax exemption on the first £30,000 of payments on termination of employment in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","62177"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681155","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-02","<p>Requested data are in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>2014-15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>53,200</p></td><td><p>56,400</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes: (1) Figures have been rounded to the nearest 100; (2) these figures do not provide a complete picture of the number of the beneficiaries of the Relief due to the fact that individuals with rental incomes below the level of the rent a room tax-free threshold (£4,250 in 2013-14 and 2014-15) do not declare these earnings; (3) figures in the table capture: (a) the number of taxpayers whose rent incomes were above the threshold and (b) those who reported using the Relief on their self-assessment tax returns for other property income.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-02-02T16:49:50.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681155/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681155/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-30","Rented Housing: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received income tax relief for renting a room in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","62178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681156","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-02","<p>The number of seafarers claiming Seafarers Earnings Deduction through self-assessment was 21,000 for the tax year 2013-14 and 20,000 for the tax year 2014-15.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-02-02T16:34:53.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681156/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681156/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-30","Shipping: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received income tax relief for Seafarers Earnings Deduction in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","62179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681157","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-02","<p>It is estimated that during 2013-14 an average of 690,000 employees received income tax relief for the three forms of employer-supported childcare. The corresponding estimate for 2014-15 is 750,000.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-02-02T16:37:45.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681157/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681157/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-30","Day care: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received income tax relief for employer-supported childcare including workplace nurseries in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","62180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681158","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-06","<p>The number of taxpayers claiming averaging adjustment (for farmers, market gardeners and creators of literary or artistic works) in 2013-14 and 2014-15 were 19,600 and 19,500 (rounded to the nearest 100) respectively.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-02-06T10:23:27.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681158/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681158/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-30","Agriculture: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received income tax relief for farming etc. averaging of profits in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","62203"
