"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681161","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-06","<p>It is estimated that around 49,000 people received Blind Persons Allowance in 2013-14 and it is projected that 48,600 people received it in 2014-15.</p><p> </p><p>These estimates are based on the 2013-14 Survey of Personal Incomes, projected to 2014-15 using economic assumptions consistent with the Office for Budget Responsibility’s November 2016 economic and fiscal outlook.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-02-06T10:22:07.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681161/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681161/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-30","Visual Impairment: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received blind person's allowance for income tax in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","62202"
