"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681164","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-06","<p>Where a local housing authority finds an applicant to be intentionally homeless, or intentionally threatened with homelessness, they have a duty to ensure the applicant is provided with advice and assistance in any attempts the applicant may make to secure, or maintain the availability of, accommodation. Where an applicant has a priority need for accommodation the authority also has a duty to secure accommodation for a period that will give the applicant a reasonable opportunity of securing accommodation for their occupation.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-06T17:43:13.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681164/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681164/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-30","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effect of the need to record people as having been made intentionally homeless on their ability to find new homes.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","62210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681165","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-07","<p>Cleaning services in buildings managed by the Department for Communities and Local Government are outsourced under a facilities management contract. Suppliers are responsible for setting rates of pay for their staff and rates for cleaners vary dependent on location and market rates. They have informed the department that they currently pay, as a minimum, the National Living Wage for cleaning the department's buildings.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-07T16:08:22.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681165/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681165/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-30","Department for Communities and Local Government: Cleaning Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the hourly pay-rate is for his Department's cleaning staff.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","62262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681166","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-06","<p>My Department is supporting the Department for Exiting the EU to deliver the Government’s overall plan for the UK to exit the EU. At present, my Department does not have any planned public consultations, White Papers or other documents to assist the UK in making effective the Government's plans for the UK to leave the EU. However, should this become necessary within the 2 year timetable for triggering Article 50, this will be reviewed.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-06T17:40:51.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681166/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681166/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-01-30","Department for Communities and Local Government: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will place in the Library a list of public consultations, White Papers and other documents his Department plans to publish to assist the UK in making effective the Government's plans for the UK to leave the EU within the two year timetable from the triggering of Article 50.","false","Biography information for Ms Gisela Stuart","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Ms Gisela Stuart","62274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681167","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-07","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer on 4 March 2016 to the hon. Member for Hornsey and Wood Green (Catherine West) to Question 28600.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-07T15:22:42.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681167/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681167/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-30","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Cleaning Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the hourly pay-rate is for her Department's cleaning staff.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","62263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681168","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Government has published a White Paper (The United Kingdom’s exit from and new partnership with the European Union). It is available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/news/a-new-positive-and-constructive-partnership-with-the-european-union</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-07T15:20:41.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681168/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681168/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-30","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will place in the Library a list of public consultations, White Papers and other documents her Department plans to publish to assist the UK in making effective the Government's plans for the UK to leave the EU within the two year timetable from the triggering of Article 50.","false","Biography information for Ms Gisela Stuart","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Ms Gisela Stuart","62275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681169","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-02","<p>The Government's strategy Sporting Future sets out that we want more people to engage in sport and physical activity and to enjoy the benefits that this brings.</p><p>The recently published Active Lives survey shows that 7,400 people in England regularly play darts.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-02-02T12:09:01.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681169/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681169/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-30","Darts: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what funding her Department has provided for the promotion and development of darts in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","62189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681170","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-02","<p>My Hon. Friend the former Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, met with MG Alba representatives on one occasion in the last 12 months, on 9th March 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Officials from my Department met with MG Alba representatives on 4 occasions during the last 12 months, on the 8th March 2016, on 9th of June 2016, on 18th July 2016 and on 1st September 2016.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-02T16:32:12.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681170/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681170/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681170/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-01-30","MG Alba","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, (a) how many times and (b) on which dates (i) Ministers and (ii) officials of her Department have met representatives of MG Alba in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","62195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681171","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-22","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) is tracking 257 allegations of breaches of International Humanitarian Law (IHL) by the Saudi-led Coalition in Yemen. Details of the MOD's analysis of these allegations are necessarily confidential.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-02-22T16:19:29.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681171/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681171/answer","Sevenoaks","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681171/answer/previousversion/34732","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681171/answer/previousversion/34732","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many allegations of humanitarian law violations by the Saudi-led coalition in Yemen his Department is tracking; and if he will place in the Library the reports relating to each such allegation.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","62165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681172","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-02","<p>Details of any UK cyber capability or operations are being withheld for the purpose of safeguarding national security.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-02T16:19:04.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681172/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681172/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","Electronic Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many offensive cyber attacks the Government has authorised since 2010.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","62181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681173","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-02","<p>The Secretary of State for Defence is responsible for authorising the military use of force in cyberspace in accordance with domestic and international law. Authorities may be delegated in accordance with the Ministry of Defence Full Spectrum Targeting Policy.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-02T16:24:51.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681173/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681173/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681173/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","Electronic Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which Ministers in his Department are responsible for authorising offensive cyber attacks on other states or terrorist groups.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","62182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681174","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-02","<p>Hightown Barracks Army Reserve Centre in Wrexham is home to the headquarters of 101 Battalion Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers. Delivered by 16 regular and Full Time Reservists, 31 reservists and eight civil servants (predominantly officers, warrant officers and senior non-commissioned officers and civilian equivalents), the headquarters provides command and administrative functions for the battalion.</p><p>In addition to the battalion headquarters, also occupying the Hightown Barracks Army Reserve Centre are a Platoon from 3rd Battalion The Royal Welsh (31 Reservists including one officer), a detachment from Wales University Officer Training Corps (two senior non-commissioned officers and 25 officer cadets) and a detachment of Clwyd and Gwynedd Army Cadet Force (four adults and 50 cadets). There are currently no plans to close this centre and the Department has consequently had no contact with developers about its future.</p><p>The Army remains committed to North Wales and in addition to those elements above in Hightown Barracks Army Reserve Centre, there will also be Army Reserve units in Colwyn Bay, Llandudno, Caenarfon, and Queensferry. The Army Cadet Force also has a wide geographic spread across the area.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","62281 ; 62282","2017-02-02T16:25:36.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681174/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681174/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681174/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","Hightown Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, (a) how many people and (b) in what roles work in the Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers at Hightown Barracks, Wrexham.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","62174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681175","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-03","<p>HQ Field Army is established for 236 military posts, which includes 188 Regular, 12 Reservists, 6 RAF/exchange posts (EXI) and 30 Full Time Reserve Service (FTRS). The tables below show breakdown by rank.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Regular Army </strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lieutenant General</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Major General</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Brigadier</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Colonel</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lieutenant Colonel</p></td><td><p>42</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Major</p></td><td><p>76</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Captain</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Warrant Officer 1</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Warrant Officer 2</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Staff Sergeant</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sergeant</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Corporal</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lance Corporal</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>188</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Reserve</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Major General</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lieutenant Colonel</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Major</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Captain</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Warrant Officer 1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>RAF/ EXI</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Colonel</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lieutenant Colonel</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Major</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wing Commander</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Squadron Leader</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>6</p></