"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681295","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-02","<p>The number of civilian staff, by civil service grade, employed by the Ministry of Defence in each year since 2010, is published in Annex Table 1b - Civilian personnel numbers by Top Level Budgetary Area1 (Head Count) in the 1 October 2016 issue of the Ministry of Defence Civilian Personnel Quarterly Statistics.</p><p>This publication can be found on the Gov.UK website at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/mod-civilian-personnel-quarterly-statistics-index</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-02T16:26:53.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681295/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681295/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681295/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many civilian staff by civil service grade were employed by his Department in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681296","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-02","<p>HMS OCEAN has a complement of 380 when in her normal operating role.</p><p>Ships' complements are not fixed; they vary, even across a class, depending on equipment fits and tasking.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-02T16:27:40.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681296/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681296/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Navy personnel are currently assigned duties aboard HMS Ocean.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62318"
