"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681305","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-03","<p>The current draft of Joint Doctrine Publication 0-30.2, Unmanned Aircraft Systems, discusses current and potential future employment of Unmanned Aircraft Systems both within and outside areas of &quot;armed conflict&quot;.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-03T14:45:19.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681305/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681305/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 16 January 2017 to Question 59205, whether he plans that JDP 0-30.2, The UK Approach to Unmanned Aircraft System, will make a distinction between the use of remotely piloted air systems (a) within and (b) outside areas of armed conflict.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","62363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681306","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-06","<p>The End of Year budget figures for the Military Provost Guard Service are provided below. The data reflects actual spend at the end of each Financial Year (FY). Data is not available for FY 2010-11</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Cost £ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>80.401</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>85.584</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>88.349</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>92.141</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>108.366</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The strength of the Military Provost Guard Service as at 1 April for the years requested is shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Strength</p></td><td><p>MPGS</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-10</p></td><td><p>2,310</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-11</p></td><td><p>2,510</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-12</p></td><td><p>2,630</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-13</p></td><td><p>2,770</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-14</p></td><td><p>2,810</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-15</p></td><td><p>2,940</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-16</p></td><td><p>2,870</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Defence Statistics (Army)</p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes/Caveats:</strong></p><p> </p><p>Figures include MPGS personnel only and therefore exclude Regular, Reserve and Gurkha personnel. Figures include all MPGS regardless of their Top Level Budget.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","62372","2017-02-06T16:54:21.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681306/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681306/answer",,,,,"http://data.p