"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681311","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-02","<p>A Maritime Task Group will be tailored to meet the required task. The precise number and mix of vessels, and therefore the number of personnel, would depend on the operational circumstances at the time.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-02T16:20:59.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681311/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681311/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel he expects to be routinely allocated to a maritime task group centred on a Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carrier as described in paragraph 4.40 in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, Cm 9161.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681312","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-06","<p>The trained strength of UK Reserve personnel in the Royal Military Police, Royal Navy Police and Royal Air Force Police as at 1 December 2016 is shown below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Service</p></td><td><p>Trained Strength of UK Reserve Forces in the UK Military Police</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Military Police</p></td><td><p>392</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Navy Police</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Air Force</p></td><td><p>148</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-06T16:52:50.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681312/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681312/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-30","Military Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the strength is of Trained UK Reserve personnel in the (a) Royal Military Police, (b) Royal Navy Police and (c) Royal Air Force Police.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681313","Department for Education","false","2017-02-07","<p>This Government has introduced the primary legislation required to allow alternative student finance, consistent with the principles of Islamic finance, to be offered alongside grants and loans. The Higher Education and Research Bill is currently before Parliament.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-02-07T17:48:18.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681313/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681313/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-01-30","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what progress her Department has made on providing student loan finance that is compliant with Islamic law.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","62352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681314","Department for Education","false","2017-02-02","<p>We will publish the Government response to the consultation on the implementation of the English Baccalaureate in due course.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-02-02T09:54:32.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681314/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681314/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-01-30","English Baccalaureate","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when her Department plans formally to respond to the consultation on Implementing the English Baccalaureate which closed on 29 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","62348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681315","Department for Education","false","2017-02-07","<p>In order to qualify for support, British nationals should generally have lived in the United Kingdom and Islands, elsewhere in the European Economic area, or in Switzerland for the three years prior to the start of their course. Satisfying this requirement demonstrates they have a substantial and recent connection with the United Kingdom, and has been upheld by the Courts as a reasonable test.</p><p>An exception to this rule is made for those who have been temporarily absent or employed overseas. This provides flexibility for students who do not meet the residence requirements but have not made a long-term decision to live outside the country.</p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-02-07T17:48:42.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681315/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681315/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-01-30","Higher Education: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that British children living abroad have the same financial help to attend British universities as children who live in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","62351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681316","Department for Education","false","2017-02-16","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring that high quality citizenship education helps to provide pupils with knowledge, skills and understanding to prepare them to play a full and active part in society.</p><p>Citizenship education is therefore part of the National Curriculum at Key Stages 3 and 4. The revised programmes of study were introduced in September 2014 and seek to direct teaching towards the core knowledge of citizenship, and to give schools more scope to decide how to teach citizenship.</p><p>The Secretary of State is considering the proposal in the White Paper regarding citizenship.</p><p>Teachers are encouraged to develop their practice with the support of specialist organisations and expert professionals such as subject associations.</p><p> </p><p>Ofsted, in its inspections of schools, considers the breadth and balance of the curriculum, including provision for pupils’ personal development, behaviour and welfare, as well as their spiritual, moral, social and cultural development. This includes how pupils develop and demonstrate skills and attitudes that will allow them to participate fully in and contribute positively to life in modern Britain. Ofsted have strengthened their inspection frameworks so that inspectors assess how well all schools protect pupils from the risks of extremism and radicalisation, and promote fundamental British values.</p><p> </p><p>We are also supporting schools to meet their obligations to protect pupils from radicalisation and promote fundamental British values, and to help them build pupils’ resilience to extremism through knowledge so that they can question information, weigh arguments, and make reasoned judgments.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently working with the Association of Citizenship Teaching on producing guidance and resources packs to help teachers lead knowledge based debates on topics relating to extremism, fundamental British values and contemporary political and social issues.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","62230","2017-02-16T14:58:32.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681316/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681316/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-01-30","Citizenship: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to review the national curriculum's citizenship programme of study as proposed in the Government's White Paper Education Excellence Everywhere, published in March 2016.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","62346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681317","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-02-02","<p>River Basin Management Plans provide the framework for protecting and improving water quality, by setting ambitious environmental goals and actions to be taken in catchments over the next 6 years and beyond. The plans were updated in 2015 and will complement the Government’s 25-year Environment Plan. This will manage the environment in a more integrated way, harnessing the potential of data, local partnerships, and environmental technology to deliver more improvements to our environment in tandem with economic growth. More information on the plans can be viewed on GOV.UK under “River Basin Management plans: 2015.”</p><p> </p><p>The current plans confirm over £3 billion investment in the water environment by 2021, which will lead to at least 680 improved water bodies by 2021, aiming for over 130 to have more abundant fish populations and 440 to have less pollution. This will be achieved through partnership working with the water industry, farmers, catchment partnerships, highways and the Coal Authority.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-02-02T10:47:10.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681317/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681317/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681317/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-01-30","Rivers: Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to reduce river pollution in the UK.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","62298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681318","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-02-02","<p>EU funding for the promotion of agricultural products is available to all member states and will continue to be available until the UK’s exit from the European Union.</p><p> </p><p>We are determined to get the best deal for Britain, including for our food and farming industry which generates over £110 billion a year for our economy.</p><p> </p><p>We will need to consider our longer-term approach to funding as part of a future domestic agricultural policy and we will ensure we consult with stakeholders in relation to any future scheme for the UK.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-02-02T11:40:48.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681318/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681318/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681318/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-01-30","Agricultural Products: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the Government plans to ensure that funding for the promotion of agricultural products continues to be made available at the level of that currently provided by the European Commission after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","62307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681319","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Government was deeply troubled by the murder of U Ko Ni. He was killed at the airport while returning from a UK-funded study trip to Indonesia. He was a leading advocate for democratic reform, and the Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Boris Johnson), met him at a reception at the British Ambassador's Residence in Rangoon during his visit to Burma on 21 January. Our Ambassador attended his funeral on 31 January. An official police investigation into U Ko Ni's death is now under way. We await its outcome. The Burmese authorities have not requested our assistance in the investigation and neither have we offered it.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","62284","2017-02-07T15:45:06.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681319/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681319/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681319/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-30","Ko Ni","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assistance he plans to offer to the Government of Burma to help it investigate the murder of Ko Ni.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Sir Hugo Swire","62285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681320","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Government was deeply troubled by the murder of U Ko Ni. He was killed at the airport while returning from a UK-funded study trip to Indonesia. He was a leading advocate for democratic reform, and the Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Boris Johnson), met him at a reception at the British Ambassador's Residence in Rangoon during his visit to Burma on 21 January. Our Ambassador attended his funeral on 31 January. An official police investigation into U Ko Ni's death is now under way. We await its outcome. The Burmese authorities have not requested our assistance in the investigation and neither have we offered it.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","62285","2017-02-07T15:45:06.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681320/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681320/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681320/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-30","Ko Ni","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Government of Burma on the murder of Ko Ni.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Sir Hugo Swire","62284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681321","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-02","<p>​The full cost of Inward State Visits is shared between a number of Government Departments.</p><p>The costs of State Visits borne by the Foreign and Commonwealth Office are published on the gov.uk website.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-02-02T16:30:12.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681321/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681321/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-30","State Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the cost is to the public purse of each of the last three state visits to the UK.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","62300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681322","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","true","2017-02-06","<p><del class="ministerial">The British Embassy responded to the Colombia Constitutional Court's judgment on 23 September 2015. No further response is necessary. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office and the British Embassy in Bogota take their employment responsibilities very seriously and pride in being an equal opportunities employer dedicated to inclusivity, a diverse workforce and valuing difference.</del></p><p><ins class="ministerial">The UK has complied with its international legal obligations, and the British Embassy responded to the Colombia Constitutional Court's judgment on 23 September 2015. No further response is necessary.</ins></p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-02-06T17:36:53.947Z","2017-02-27T12:28:10.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681322/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681322/answer","Rutland and Melton ; Rutland and Melton","Rutland and Melton ; Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan ; Sir Alan Duncan","Sir Alan Duncan ; Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681322/answer/previousversion/33866 ; http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681322/answer/previousversion/34309","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan ; Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681322/answer/previousversion/33866 ; http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681322/answer/previousversion/34309","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan ; Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-30","Colombia: Embassies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, by what date the UK Embassy in Bogota plans to comply with the Colombia Constitutional Court's judgment in the case of 