"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681323","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-06","<p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs has received assurances that all British passport holders remain able to travel to the United States, and the Executive Order makes no difference to any British passport-holder, irrespective of their country of birth or whether they hold another passport. Questions about non-uk passport holders are a matter for the government of the USA.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-02-06T17:33:18.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681323/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681323/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681323/answer","Rutland and Melton","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681323/answer/previousversion/33873","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681323/answer/previousversion/33873","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-30","USA: Travel Restrictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of whether the recent Executive Order on travel to the US applies to people resident in the UK who were born in Somaliland and (a) are British citizens, (b) are citizens of another EEA country, (c) have indefinite leave to remain in the UK and (d) have another immigration status.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","62377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681324","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-07","<p>The UK Government is working to support the Kenyan authorities in our shared aim of reducing the threat from terrorism. Our support enhances Kenya's capability to disrupt terrorist threats, gather evidence and make arrests. We do not provide direct funding to the Anti-Terrorism Police Unit, but support capacity building in investigative skills, operations management, forensics and evidence recovery as well as infrastructure. Respect for human rights and adherence to the law form key components of all our engagement.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-07T14:21:32.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681324/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681324/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681324/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-01-30","Kenya: Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what funding and other support the Government has provided to the Kenyan Anti-Terrorism Police Unit in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","62359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681325","Department of Health","false","2017-02-02","<p>Since January 2016, the date of birth of all people admitted to adult inpatient mental health wards has been routinely collected via the Mental Health Services Data Set by NHS Digital. Age can be derived from this patient level data.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","62391","2017-02-02T18:00:53.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681325/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681325/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/681325/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-30","Mental Health Services: Hospital Beds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 27 January 2017 to Question 61521, what information his Department holds on the ages of people admitted to adult in-patient mental health wards.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","62390"
